#: plugins/ip_cam/templates/ip_cam_help.html:61
msgid "GIF notes"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/ip_cam/templates/ip_cam_help.html:62
msgid "A GIF is created from successful JPEG downloads. If it contains fewer frames than expected, check the JPEG test and the diagnostics counters. A camera that fails every few downloads will naturally produce fewer usable frames. GIF frames are normalized to one size and resized so the final animation stays under Maximum image size when possible. Existing oversized GIF files are regenerated from cached frames when they are used and frames are available. The GIF preview keeps the original aspect ratio, so it should not be distorted by the browser."
